title: Eco-car wins eight Indonesian students their F1 dream
text:
Media playback is unsupported on your device Eco-car wins eight Indonesian students their F1 dream 7 February 2017 Last updated at 23:53 GMT 
Eight Indonesian engineering students from modest backgrounds won an international competition to design an eco-car. 
They won the competition on their fourth attempt and got to spend a week with Ferrari in Italy at the famous Fiorano F1 test circuit. 
Reporting by Endang Nurdin, Filming by Maher Nakhla in Italy and Oki Budhi in Indonesia Related Topics
